	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>&#8222;Bank Venezuela&#8221;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Puerto Cabello</placeName>&#44; <date>Septr 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1854</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your esteemed lines <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> July</date> could not be acknow&#45;<lb/>ledged by the Dallett because I was rather unwell<lb/> at the departure of said vessel.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I thank you extremely for the portrait and also<lb/> for the books&#44; the amount &#36;9.38 will be handed<lb/> to you by <persName>Messrs. Dallett Brothers</persName> as per enclosed<lb/> order</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I regret exceedingly that I am not able to procure<lb/> the palms and citrons for you&#59; I have sent a man<lb/> to the country and he returned saying that neither<lb/> of the two could be found.  I trust that this fail&#45;<lb/>ure will not discourage you to command my ser&#45;<lb/>&#45;vice in future.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If God please I will leave this about next week<lb/> to pass <date>Kipur</date> in <placeName>Cura&#231;ao</placeName> and will stay there<lb/> four about six weeks&#44; as my eldest son will complete<lb/> his thirteenth year&#44; and according to usage he is<lb/> preparing to read a portion of the law&#44; which<lb/> law I trust that himself and all my other chil&#45;<lb/>dren will ever love and respect.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you can find a print of the Temple oblige<lb/> me to procure one for me&#44; and have it put in a<lb/> rose wood frame with gilt edges.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>I wish yourself and family long life and prospe<lb/>&#45;rity and that you all may be written in the book<lb/> of life &#38;c Is the sincere wish of</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours&#44; faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">A Myerston</persName></p>
				<p><date>Septr 25th</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are but very few Israelites here&#44; but we do<lb/> not feel the less for our brethren in the <placeName>Holy Land</placeName>.<lb/>  Our eldest <persName>Mr David Lobo</persName> is momently expected from<lb/> the Interior and on his arrival we intend to meet<lb/> with the object of succouring our above mentioned bro&#45;<lb/>thers.  Our contribution will be very scanty because we<lb/> are most all men of family and depending entirely<lb/> in our gains as clerks and petty merchants for a<lb/> <sic>subsistance</sic>&#59; were we in affluence we would be as<lb/> generous as our other brothers abroad&#44; but none of us<lb/> has the means of being liberal&#59; however&#44; we are never<lb/> behind in contributing with our might to the cause<lb/> of humanity</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">A M</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>&#8222;Bank Venezuela&#8221;</p>
				<p><addressee>Reverd Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
